.TH wxFilePickerCtrl 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxFilePickerCtrl \- This control allows the user to select a file.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The generic implementation is a button which brings up a \fIwxFileDialog\fR when clicked. Native implementation may differ but this is usually a (small) widget which give access to the file-chooser dialog. It is only available if \fIwxUSE_FILEPICKERCTRL\fR is set to 1 (the default).

.SS "Styles"

.PP
This class supports the following styles:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFLP_DEFAULT_STYLE: The default style: includes wxFLP_OPEN | wxFLP_FILE_MUST_EXIST and, under wxMSW and wxOSX, wxFLP_USE_TEXTCTRL.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFLP_USE_TEXTCTRL: Creates a text control to the left of the picker button which is completely managed by the \fIwxFilePickerCtrl\fR and which can be used by the user to specify a path (see SetPath). The text control is automatically synchronized with button's value. Use functions defined in \fIwxPickerBase\fR to modify the text control.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFLP_OPEN: Creates a picker which allows the user to select a file to open.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFLP_SAVE: Creates a picker which allows the user to select a file to save.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFLP_OVERWRITE_PROMPT: Can be combined with wxFLP_SAVE only: ask confirmation to the user before selecting a file.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFLP_FILE_MUST_EXIST: Can be combined with wxFLP_OPEN only: the file selected in the popup \fIwxFileDialog\fR must be an existing file. Notice that it still remains possible for the user to enter a non-existent file name in the text control if \fIwxFLP_USE_TEXTCTRL\fR is also used, this flag is a hint for the user rather than a guarantee that the selected file does exist for the program.

.RE


